## Summary: Describe in one sentence, what it is and what it does? (max 120 characters)

GIS help you to integrate the spatial dimention (where) to your data analyses

## Instructions: How is it used for R&amp;D? What steps to follow?

It is used for R&amp;D to geolocate physical elements or to model abstract elements. To use it, we need to mobilize data collection tools to collect data and use a GIS software (open source or commercial) to analyze this data and generate information.

## Requirements: What is needed to effectively use it for R&amp;D? (e.g. skills, conditions, inputs, resources)

We need technical skill in georeferenced data collection and analyses + Soft skill in problem solving

When using GIS tools for R&amp;D, we need to keep in mind principle apply for information Management in general.
